Description: Fragment of oval handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora to sharpish turn. Clay fine pink-buff; cream slip. Rectangular stamp.
Curator's comments: Petrie Diary (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 134, 2. Name Dorotheos.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0890)
